metadata.name: Tegel
metadata.description:
A tilt-shift portrait of the now decommissioned Berlin Tegel Airport (TXL) air traffic control tower. 

Designed in the 1960's by Meinhard von Gerkan and Volkwin Marg, the main terminal of the brutalist style airport was a hollow hexagon shape - a functional choice as well as an aesthetic one which informed the rest of the design.

This image was made in 2018.

5000X6000px
